items.title: Lenovo reports a 5% fall in Q2 profit
items.description: Lenovo reported a 5% decline in its second-quarter profit, even as revenue rose to $20.5 billion, slightly above market expectations. Net profit came in at $340 million, missing analyst estimates.

items.title: Nvidia's profit jumps 65% to $31.9 billion. Is it enough for Wall Street?
items.description: On Wednesday, Nvidia provided a reminder of just how much the world craves those chips. The company said that in its most recent quarter, its profit was $31.9 billion, up 65% from a year ago and 245% from the year before that. Among the tech industry's giants, only Google's parent company, Alphabet, made more money in the same quarter.

items.title: Nvidia's strong forecast calms AI bubble jitters - for now
items.description: The results calmed - at least temporarily - investor nerves frayed over concerns that an AI boom has outrun fundamentals. Global markets have looked to the chip designer to determine whether investing billions of dollars in AI infrastructure expansion has resulted in an AI bubble.
